  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0bcb\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Indictment filed against Johnston",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Minister Johnston Fernando and three others who have been named as defendants in the corruption case were indicted today (30) in the presence of Colombo High Court Judge Aditya Patabendike.",
        "During 2012, a case was filed against the trio for allegedly causing loss to the government by using the employees of Sathosa for political activities.",
        "The case was filed against former minister Johnston Fernando, former chairman of Lanka Sathosa Corporation Eraj Fernando and Johnston's private secretary Raj Mohidin Mohd Sakir.",
        "The chargesheet was shared today while the case filed by the commission probing allegations of bribery or corruption was taken up.",
        "Also, the judge ordered the release of the three defendants on two body bonds worth Rs 50 lakh each and fixed October 21 as the date for the hearing of evidence in the case.",
        "The Commission to Investigate Allegations of Bribery or Corruption has filed four charges under Section 70 of the Bribery Act against the three accused.",
        "The Commission has accused the first Prime Minister, Johnston Fernando, of engaging Satoshi employees illegally for election work during his tenure as Minister of Cooperatives and Domestic Trade in 2012.",
        "The commission filed a new charge sheet in the Colombo High Court on May 30, in place of the previously withdrawn charge sheet.",
        "It is noteworthy that the Colombo Chief Magistrate's Court on January 28 ordered the acquittal of three persons, including Johnston Fernando, from corruption cases after the commission decided to withdraw the charge sheet due to a technical glitch."
      ],
